<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-18T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-18T03:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 <persName>Hrinkevich,
                                Frank</persName>/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DJE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davies</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-18T11:00:00+03:00">October
                                    18, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 18—8:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>268. In a note dated October 16, the Foreign Office advises the Embassy
                            of the arrest on July 19, 1937, under [article] 58 (10) of the Criminal
                            Code of <persName>Frank Hrinkevich</persName> who is now under detention
                            at Minsk. His passport (number 85071 of March 31, 1934) has been in the
                            custody of the Embassy since March 16, 1937, on which date it was
                            received from the Foreign Office with the request that it be renewed as
                            the Soviet Government desired to expel him from the Soviet Union for
                            having “committed systematic violations of the regulations in force” in
                            that country. Efforts will be made to have <persName corresp="#p_DE2">Durbrow</persName> interview him at Minsk on October 22nd.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJE1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Davies</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>